    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card text-center bg-dark mt-3">
    <div class="card-header bg-dark">
      <ul class="nav nav-pills card-header-pills nav-fill bg-dark">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link btn btn-outline-success pickShaper" id="shaperText">Shaper</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link btn btn-outline-info pickCriminal" id="criminalText">Criminal</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link btn btn-outline-danger pickAnarch" id="anarchText">Anarch</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link btn btn-outline-warning pickMini" id="miniText">Mini-Factions</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body shaperInfo">
      <p class="card-text text-success"><em>Shapers</em> are planners. They'll put their head down and come up
        with a way to
        solve
        whatever
        problem
        the corp is
        presenting them with. This takes time. If the corp does their thing before the Shaper comes up with a
        solution,
        corp wins. Otherwise the Shaper gets to run all over them.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body criminalInfo d-none">
      <p class="card-text text-info"><em>Criminals</em> are sneaky bastards. They don't want to deal with ICE
        and prefer to bypass it or
        find
        another
        way
        around it. They're great at making money and denying the corp's funds but horribly inefficient at breaking
        ICE.
        The longer they can make the corp take to setup, the happier a Criminal is.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body anarchInfo d-none">
      <p class="card-text text-danger"><em>Anarchs</em> will smash a window with their face to see what'll
        happen. They can do most things
        and do
        them
        well but
        at great personal cost. Smart Anarchs mitigate the costs. Other Anarchs try to win before the costs get
        too
        great.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body miniInfo d-none">
      <p class="card-text text-warning">
        The <em>Mini-Factions</em> are certainly an eclectic bunch. They each borrow familiar traits from each
        faction, but put their own unique twist on things. Are you a Bioroid following your programmed directives?
        Are you corrupted source code turned sentient looking to devour everything in your path? Or are you the
        badass
        Mother working with the best security corporations to gauge corporate weaknesses?
      </p>
    </div>
